---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Questions & Answers | River Roots Studio" description="Frequently asked questions about River Roots Studio workshops, pricing, and creative process.">
  <!-- PAGE HEADER -->
  <section class="relative w-full overflow-hidden" style="height: clamp(300px, 35vw, 400px);">
    <img
      src="/images/faq-mugs.jpg"
      alt="Two ceramic mugs on a wooden table"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-center"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.35);"></div>
    <div class="relative h-full flex items-center justify-center px-4">
      <h1 class="text-[4rem] sm:text-[5rem] font-semibold leading-tight text-center" style="font-family: var(--font-accent); color: #ffffff; text-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);">
        Questions &amp; Answers
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Q&A BODY -->
  <section class="py-10 sm:py-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-10">

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-moss mb-2">Why don&rsquo;t you give exact times for your workshops to begin and end?</h2>
        <p class="text-brown/80 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          I give very close estimates. Each gathering of people brings their own experience, which affects the pace I guide.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-moss mb-2">Is this a charity or a business?</h2>
        <p class="text-brown/80 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          For now it is a charity. I&rsquo;m dealing with a chronic illness that can influence me giving you my best. Worst case, I am not my amazing self, and your donation helps children in need through <a href="https://www.savethechildren.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-moss hover:text-moss-dark underline transition-colors">Save the Children</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-moss mb-2">Why do you sometimes ask us to use our non-dominant hand and other times not?</h2>
        <p class="text-brown/80 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Art therapists use the science of non-dominant hand writing for emotional issues. Expressive Arts uses many methods to guide our brain toward our intuitive knowing with the lightness of curiosity; the power of the &ldquo;other&rdquo; hand is only one of them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-moss mb-2">Why are your workshops limited to six people?</h2>
        <p class="text-brown/80 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          This is not a &ldquo;side-hustle&rdquo; but a dream to share the things that have made my inner world more grounded, living in a world of uncertainty.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-moss mb-2">Why don&rsquo;t you show images of the art we&rsquo;ll be making?</h2>
        <p class="text-brown/80 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The images of what you will create are unique to you and how you feel on that day. The images of my studio may reveal the sense of place, and hopefully the sanctuary of giving yourself this time.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
